♪ It seems today
that all you see ♪

00:04.972 --> 00:08.107
♪ Is violence in movies
and sex on TV ♪

00:08.109 --> 00:11.810
♪ But where are those
good old-fashioned values ♪

00:11.812 --> 00:14.813
♪ On which we used to rely?

00:14.815 --> 00:18.183
♪ Lucky there's a family guy

00:18.185 --> 00:21.553
♪ Lucky there's a man
who positively can do ♪

00:21.555 --> 00:23.022
♪ All the things that make us

00:23.024 --> 00:24.490
♪ Laugh and cry

00:24.492 --> 00:30.062
♪ He's... a...
Fam... ily... Guy! ♪

00:36.803 --> 00:39.471
ANNOUNCER: <i>Do you want an excuse</i>
<i>to not go home this Christmas?</i>

00:39.473 --> 00:41.373
<i>Then fly Northwest Airlines.</i>

00:41.375 --> 00:44.076
<i>At Northwest Airlines,</i>
<i>thousands of employees</i>

00:44.078 --> 00:46.845
<i>are dedicated to delaying</i>
<i>and cancelling flights</i>

00:46.847 --> 00:48.881
<i>so you won't get home</i>
<i>for the holidays.</i>

00:48.883 --> 00:51.817
No way I'm getting you
on your connecting flight.

00:51.819 --> 00:53.919
No way we're taking off on time.

00:53.921 --> 00:57.089
Don't worry, I'm taking
this flight back to the gate.

00:57.091 --> 00:59.758
Do you think Jeff will
make it home this year?

00:59.760 --> 01:02.161
<i>No way--</i>
<i>because Jeff flew Northwest.</i>

01:02.163 --> 01:03.362
Thanks, Northwest.

01:03.364 --> 01:04.997
I hate my family.

01:04.999 --> 01:07.099
Ah, that looks great.

01:07.101 --> 01:10.102
You know, I think this is gonna
be our best Christmas ever.

01:10.104 --> 01:11.837
Yeah, but don't get
your hopes up, Lois.

01:11.839 --> 01:14.106
I couldn't afford to get you
what I got you last year.

01:14.108 --> 01:15.574
I know how you
like that song,

01:15.576 --> 01:17.376
so I got you two
turtledoves.

01:17.378 --> 01:19.778
Where did you get these?

01:19.780 --> 01:22.381
I went to a scientist and had
them genetically engineered.

01:22.383 --> 01:24.049
Fly, beautiful turtledoves.

01:24.051 --> 01:25.951
Bring Christmas cheer to all.

01:25.953 --> 01:28.287
(turtlesdoves screeching,
all yelling)

01:28.289 --> 01:30.456
Everybody outside-- we'll do
the rest of Christmas outside!

01:30.458 --> 01:32.191
Go, go, go!

01:32.193 --> 01:36.228
Look, Stewie, I'm hanging the
ornament you made at preschool.

01:36.230 --> 01:37.463
Just hang it up.

01:37.465 --> 01:39.031
Why do you have to narrate
everything you do?

01:39.033 --> 01:41.066
Peter, you want to put
the star on top of the...

01:41.068 --> 01:43.202
Hang on, hang on, Lois,
I always wanted to do this.

01:43.204 --> 01:46.105
Wait a second.

01:46.107 --> 01:48.273
It's coming.

01:48.275 --> 01:50.375
There it is!

01:52.579 --> 01:53.812
Huh?

01:53.814 --> 01:55.047
Eh, it's something,

01:55.049 --> 01:56.915
but you still
got a leftover "R."

01:56.917 --> 01:58.050
This was hard.

01:58.052 --> 01:59.885
I did this for you!

02:01.087 --> 02:02.654
This one's my favorite ornament.

02:02.656 --> 02:05.257
I can only imagine what it
must have been like for them

02:05.259 --> 02:07.126
on that very first Christmas.

02:07.128 --> 02:08.827
Yeah, it was probably
very moving...

02:08.829 --> 02:09.895
and fictional.

02:09.897 --> 02:11.597
Jesus lived with us
for, like, a week.

02:11.599 --> 02:13.165
What else do you need?

02:13.167 --> 02:15.467
It's the greatest
story ever told, Meg.

02:15.469 --> 02:18.003
A story that goes back
over a hundred years.

02:18.005 --> 02:20.639
Yay, <i>Star Wars!</i>
<i>No, Chris.</i>

02:20.641 --> 02:24.176
It's the story of Christmas
and the Immaculate Conception.

02:24.178 --> 02:25.644
You guys were born
the dirty way.

02:25.646 --> 02:29.081
Now, gather around, everybody,
and hear the awe-inspiring tale

02:29.083 --> 02:32.184
that's caused millions
and millions of deaths.

02:32.186 --> 02:34.119
Many years ago
there was a hardworking

02:34.121 --> 02:36.088
<i>young carpenter named Joseph,</i>

02:36.090 --> 02:38.757
<i>and one day, Joseph and his</i>
<i>friend Robby were hanging...</i>

02:38.759 --> 02:40.692
CHRIS:
Guy's name was Robby back then?

02:40.694 --> 02:42.261
PETER:
<i>The Bible is fuzzy on that.</i>

02:42.263 --> 02:43.862
<i>Anyway, Joseph and Robby</i>
<i>were hanging out</i>

02:43.864 --> 02:45.531
<i>one day when this happened...</i>

02:45.533 --> 02:47.933
So, I went to see that new
Oedipus play last week.

02:47.935 --> 02:50.469
Took my mother-- talk
about an awkward ride home.

02:50.471 --> 02:51.970
Barely got a good-night kiss.

02:51.972 --> 02:54.039
Hey, Joseph,
check it out.

02:57.177 --> 02:59.878
Oh, my God,
look at that body.

02:59.880 --> 03:02.881
Can't you just imagine her
standing on people's front lawns

03:02.883 --> 03:04.349
inside a cut-in-half bathtub?

03:04.351 --> 03:07.452
You should go talk to her
and see if she can talk.

03:07.454 --> 03:10.389
Uh, hi.
I'm... I'm Joseph.

03:10.391 --> 03:12.524
Oh, hello. I'm Mary.

03:12.526 --> 03:16.128
Listen, um, I was wondering if
you'd like to go out sometime.

03:16.130 --> 03:18.230
Well, sure.
That sounds nice.

03:18.232 --> 03:20.299
You know, there's
a beautiful spot outside of town

03:20.301 --> 03:22.167
where they dump
all the foreskins.

03:22.169 --> 03:24.736
You can sit on top
and watch the sunset.

03:24.738 --> 03:26.171
Oh, great, and maybe
we could slaughter a lamb

03:26.173 --> 03:28.073
and light it on fire
so that it rains.

03:28.075 --> 03:30.242
Well, let's not
go too fast.

03:30.244 --> 03:32.177
Listen, I'll see
you later, okay?

03:32.179 --> 03:33.912
I've got to go sit in a
circle with the other women

03:33.914 --> 03:36.248
and stare off
into the fields.

03:36.250 --> 03:37.916
All right,
you got a date.

03:37.918 --> 03:40.152
Yeah, I just hope it goes
better than my last one.

03:40.154 --> 03:42.487
Wow, Joseph,
that was great.

03:42.489 --> 03:44.656
Yeah, I got to say
I'm a little disappointed.

03:44.658 --> 03:46.191
When you said I could do you
in your "mudhut,"

03:46.193 --> 03:48.227
I thought you meant
something else.

03:49.696 --> 03:51.396
PETER:
<i>And so Mary and Joseph</i>
<i>began their courtship.</i>

03:51.398 --> 03:53.999
<i>But even after several dates,</i>

03:54.001 --> 03:55.934
<i>Joseph couldn't get</i>
<i>to first base.</i>

03:55.936 --> 03:57.436
<i>Not just because</i>
<i>Mary was a virgin,</i>

03:57.438 --> 04:00.339
<i>but because baseball would not</i>
<i>be invented for 1,800 years</i>

04:00.341 --> 04:02.507
<i>and nobody knew what the hell</i>
<i>he was talking about.</i>

04:02.509 --> 04:05.844
You know this is the same picnic
basket we drowned my sister in.

04:05.846 --> 04:07.346
It was back when they were like,
"Drown all the girls,"

04:07.348 --> 04:09.414
and then they were like,
"Don't drown all the girls,"

04:09.416 --> 04:12.851
but she was born on a
drowning week, so, you know.

04:12.853 --> 04:14.186
(sneezes)

04:14.188 --> 04:17.289
Oh, look at that--
there's hardly any blood.

04:17.291 --> 04:18.557
You're very healthy.

04:18.559 --> 04:20.592
Well, I try
to take care of myself.

04:20.594 --> 04:23.295
Joseph, this is the most
fun I've had in a while.

04:23.297 --> 04:24.963
That's good, that's good.

04:24.965 --> 04:26.698
Pull your pants down.
What?

04:26.700 --> 04:28.400
Come on, this is
our seventh date.

04:28.402 --> 04:29.801
It's completely natural.

04:29.803 --> 04:31.403
Birds do it, bees do it,

04:31.405 --> 04:33.405
dinosaurs whom we live
alongside do it.

04:33.407 --> 04:34.773
Joseph, I can't.

04:34.775 --> 04:36.275
People will talk.

04:36.277 --> 04:37.709
So, what?
They'll talk in Aramaic.

04:37.711 --> 04:39.111
Do you understand that?
I don't.

04:39.113 --> 04:42.414
Look, you're very sweet,
but I have to save myself.

04:42.416 --> 04:45.150
For who? There's only
30 people in the whole world

04:45.152 --> 04:47.052
and you're related
to half of them.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.987
I can't believe how hard
you're making me work.

04:48.989 --> 04:51.923
Well, I do have
a very good virginity coach.

04:51.925 --> 04:54.226
No, no, no.

04:54.228 --> 04:56.328
Okay, I think I got it.
How's this?

04:56.330 --> 05:00.332
(imitating):
No, no, no.

05:00.334 --> 05:04.002
No, no, no.

05:04.004 --> 05:05.337
Look, I can't explain it,

05:05.339 --> 05:07.506
but something is
telling me to wait.

05:07.508 --> 05:10.008
Something deep,
deep inside of me.

05:10.010 --> 05:11.610
Stop talking like that
or I swear to God

05:11.612 --> 05:13.312
I'm gonna Pompeii
all over this blanket.

05:13.314 --> 05:15.013
(laughing):
Oh, you're silly.

05:15.015 --> 05:17.316
Come on, let's
just watch the show.

05:17.318 --> 05:20.319
(all shouting angrily)

05:20.321 --> 05:21.787
Wow, she's really getting it.

05:21.789 --> 05:24.189
Yeah, I know that girl--
that's Donna Magdalene,

05:24.191 --> 05:27.392
and her sister's a
bigger slut than she is.

05:31.264 --> 05:34.266
You know, we Jews got it right,
working with our hands.

05:34.268 --> 05:36.868
Yeah, let those eggheads
in Rome do the brain work,

05:36.870 --> 05:38.837
we Jews will do
the brawn work.

05:38.839 --> 05:41.106
Hey, Italians, put a book
down once in a while.

05:41.108 --> 05:42.341
Yeah, yeah, right.
Definitely, yeah.

05:42.343 --> 05:43.942
Put a book down.

05:43.944 --> 05:45.377
Hey, so, uh,
you've been seeing

05:45.379 --> 05:47.312
