12:45.766 --> 12:47.198
(Announcer laughing)

12:47.200 --> 12:49.033
ANNOUNCER:
<i>And introducing that joke!</i>

12:49.035 --> 12:51.102
Ben-Him and Ben-Her!

12:51.104 --> 12:53.638
<i>Even Noah wouldn't put</i>
<i>these two together!</i>

12:53.640 --> 12:55.640
Cover your privates!

12:55.642 --> 12:57.542
Everyone can coli-see-um!

13:00.880 --> 13:02.647
PETER:
<i>Meanwhile, the three wise men</i>

13:02.649 --> 13:04.916
<i>were making their way</i>
<i>across the desert.</i>

13:04.918 --> 13:06.384
Hey, did you hear
they're coming out

13:06.386 --> 13:08.052
with four more
Commandments?

13:08.054 --> 13:10.288
Uch, all that stuff does is
interfere with small business.

13:10.290 --> 13:13.224
Oh, no, we're
out of water.

13:13.226 --> 13:14.425
We gotta
stop somewhere.

13:14.427 --> 13:16.427
Look. That's
King Herod's palace.

13:16.429 --> 13:18.229
Maybe we can get
water over there.

13:18.231 --> 13:20.932
QUAGMIRE:
Wow, look at that classy,
Middle Eastern house

13:20.934 --> 13:22.433
with gold and marble.

13:22.435 --> 13:24.302
People will always want
to live next

13:24.304 --> 13:26.938
to big Middle Eastern houses
with gold and marble.

13:26.940 --> 13:29.607
Uch, I'm so bored.

13:29.609 --> 13:30.775
How's the TV coming?

13:30.777 --> 13:33.178
We are a long way off.

13:33.180 --> 13:34.612
Excuse me.

13:34.614 --> 13:37.816
We are three wise men
on a long journey.

13:37.818 --> 13:39.417
Could we trouble you
for some water?

13:39.419 --> 13:42.320
Sure. Not quite wise enough
to pack any, huh?

13:42.322 --> 13:43.955
So, what brings you to Judea?

13:43.957 --> 13:46.357
We're on our way to Bethlehem
to see a magic baby.

13:46.359 --> 13:47.859
Magic baby?
What's he do,

13:47.861 --> 13:49.294
card tricks,
rabbit in the hat?

13:49.296 --> 13:50.662
Would he let someone
in the audience

13:50.664 --> 13:51.996
punch him in
the stomach?

13:51.998 --> 13:53.998
I'd like to punch a
baby in the stomach.

13:54.000 --> 13:55.333
You can't punch
this baby.

13:55.335 --> 13:56.534
He's the Messiah.

13:56.536 --> 13:58.603
Yes, they're even calling him
the King of Kings.

13:58.605 --> 14:00.471
Yuck.
He already sounds like a dick.

14:00.473 --> 14:02.106
Okay, then how about this?

14:02.108 --> 14:03.675
I'm the King of King
of Kings.

14:03.677 --> 14:05.109
Ha! New name! Called it!

14:05.111 --> 14:07.212
Sounds like somebody's
a little threatened.

14:07.214 --> 14:09.848
No, I'm not. Would a guy who
feels threatened make sure

14:09.850 --> 14:11.382
all his advisors
are shorter than him?

14:11.384 --> 14:13.117
Ha! You said
it, King!

14:13.119 --> 14:14.219
That's telling him!

14:14.221 --> 14:15.320
Big guy!

14:15.322 --> 14:17.222
You know what?
Still, just to be safe,

14:17.224 --> 14:19.290
I should probably kill
that baby.

14:19.292 --> 14:21.793
Then Jodie Foster will love me.

14:24.997 --> 14:26.297
Welcome to the
Motel Shiksa.

14:26.299 --> 14:28.233
We won't leave the
light on for you,

14:28.235 --> 14:30.501
because what, do I work
for the electric company?

14:30.503 --> 14:32.904
Yes, we were wondering
if you had a room available?

14:32.906 --> 14:35.173
Sorry, we're all booked up--
Cher's in town.

14:35.175 --> 14:37.208
You won't find a room
in the city.

14:37.210 --> 14:39.477
No room? Joseph,
what are we gonna do?

14:39.479 --> 14:41.646
Don't worry.
I got this covered.

14:41.648 --> 14:43.314
No rooms, eh?

14:43.316 --> 14:46.150
Well, perhaps you have a room
for my good friend

14:46.152 --> 14:47.752
fistful of sand.

14:47.754 --> 14:48.887
Where's your money?

14:48.889 --> 14:50.255
I spent it on sand.

14:50.257 --> 14:51.856
I'm sorry,
I can't help you.

14:51.858 --> 14:53.057
But, sir, please,

14:53.059 --> 14:55.693
my wife is with child
and about to give birth.

14:55.695 --> 14:58.329
And I am with burrito
and about to do the same.

14:58.331 --> 15:02.200
Sir, if you don't leave now,
I'm gonna have to call IX-I-I.

15:02.202 --> 15:04.168
Yeah, we, we did one
of those earlier.

15:04.170 --> 15:05.403
Yours is better, though.

15:05.405 --> 15:07.272
We probably should've waited
for yours.

15:07.274 --> 15:09.207
(groaning)

15:09.209 --> 15:10.508
Joseph, my water
just broke!

15:10.510 --> 15:11.843
It's time!

15:11.845 --> 15:13.111
Oh, my God!

15:13.113 --> 15:15.380
Please, you've gotta
have <i>some</i> place for us!

15:15.382 --> 15:16.514
We're desperate!

15:16.516 --> 15:19.050
Well, there's
a manger out back.

15:19.052 --> 15:20.785
You can stay there.

15:20.787 --> 15:22.387
That's fine, that's fine!
We'll take it!

15:22.389 --> 15:24.122
CHER (in distance):
Bethlehem!

15:24.124 --> 15:26.291
I have one question for you!

15:26.293 --> 15:27.458
(pop song plays)

15:27.460 --> 15:31.396
♪ Do you believe in life
after love? ♪

15:31.398 --> 15:34.365
Dah... See?
I told you she'd open with that.

15:39.071 --> 15:42.473
So, Joseph and Mary
were turned away
from the inn.

15:42.475 --> 15:43.908
But, Dad, I still
don't understand

15:43.910 --> 15:45.543
the whole Immaculate
Conception thing.

15:45.545 --> 15:48.112
How can anyone get pregnant
without having sex?

15:48.114 --> 15:49.881
Oh, there's lots of
stories of that, Meg.

15:49.883 --> 15:51.382
Cleveland's got
a cousin who had

15:51.384 --> 15:52.784
eight girlfriends
get pregnant,

15:52.786 --> 15:55.119
and he says he's not
responsible for a single one.

15:55.121 --> 15:56.788
Good guy.
You shake his hand,

15:56.790 --> 15:58.890
it feels like you're
touching a nice briefcase.

15:58.892 --> 16:01.125
But back to our story.

16:04.563 --> 16:06.497
All right, here we are.

16:06.499 --> 16:07.999
This seems pretty gross.

16:08.001 --> 16:10.768
I can't believe my baby's
gonna be the Son of God.

16:10.770 --> 16:13.004
Looks like all those
years fighting off

16:13.006 --> 16:15.640
my own father's advances
have finally paid off.

16:15.642 --> 16:17.141
What shall we name him?

16:17.143 --> 16:18.943
Well, this is kinda
like a barn.

16:18.945 --> 16:20.478
We could call
him Barney.

16:20.480 --> 16:21.479
Yeah, maybe.

16:21.481 --> 16:23.014
Or I kinda always
liked Tristan.

16:23.016 --> 16:24.349
Oh, my God, you want him

16:24.351 --> 16:25.917
to get the crap
beat out of him?

16:25.919 --> 16:28.086
They will crucify him
with a name like that.

16:28.088 --> 16:29.921
No, no, no.

16:29.923 --> 16:31.923
What are you doing?
How long you been there?

16:31.925 --> 16:33.791
Those names is no good.

16:33.793 --> 16:35.960
Look, why don't y'all
just give me a list,

16:35.962 --> 16:38.496
I'll run 'em up to God,
and see if he picks one.

16:38.498 --> 16:40.631
No... no...

16:40.633 --> 16:42.700
That's the name
of a champagne.

16:42.702 --> 16:44.102
No... no...

16:44.104 --> 16:45.003
Terrible!

16:45.005 --> 16:46.304
These are all
just terrible!

16:46.306 --> 16:47.505
Relax, God.

16:47.507 --> 16:49.974
You want me to get y'all
some wine and cheeses?

16:49.976 --> 16:51.709
Wait, what'd you
just say?

16:51.711 --> 16:55.380
Cheeses.
You want some cheeses?

16:55.382 --> 16:57.015
And that's why you're
allowed to eat

16:57.017 --> 17:01.853
as much mozzarella as
you want in any church.

17:01.855 --> 17:04.889
<i>So the three wise men set off</i>
<i>again on their journey.</i>

17:04.891 --> 17:06.190
You sure this is
the right way?

17:06.192 --> 17:09.027
Yes, I'm sure.
We follow the star.

17:09.029 --> 17:10.895
Are you sure
that's a star?

17:10.897 --> 17:12.397
We've had this
conversation!

17:12.399 --> 17:13.998
Yes, it's a star!

17:14.000 --> 17:15.566
It's got flashing
red lights!

17:15.568 --> 17:18.002
Oh, my God!
It <i>is</i> a (bleep) plane!

17:18.004 --> 17:20.238
And I said that yesterday,
you stupid idiot!

17:22.408 --> 17:24.542
Hey, thanks for coming out
on such late notice, Doc.

17:24.544 --> 17:27.078
Oh, you don't
have to thank me.
This is a big deal.

17:27.080 --> 17:29.847
It's not every day
that God bestows a
woman with his son.

17:29.849 --> 17:31.816
Has it ever
happened before?
Yeah, once.

17:31.818 --> 17:33.584
But the woman drank
during her pregnancy.

17:33.586 --> 17:35.420
The kid came out
a real lemon.

17:35.422 --> 17:38.189
I turned this
water into poo!

17:38.191 --> 17:39.690
Uh-huh.

17:39.692 --> 17:42.060
I also turned this
fish into poo!

17:42.062 --> 17:43.594
Ah...

17:43.596 --> 17:45.430
Do you want your
birthday present?

17:45.432 --> 17:47.932
I think I know
what it is.

17:47.934 --> 17:50.668
(laughs) It's a
cashmere sweater.

17:50.670 --> 17:51.903
Oh, wow!

17:51.905 --> 17:55.706
That's actually
really nice.

17:55.708 --> 17:56.707
And now it's poo!

17:56.709 --> 17:58.009
(shrieks)

18:00.612 --> 18:02.447
Well, here we are.

18:02.449 --> 18:03.781
Okay, guys,
squeeze in.

18:03.783 --> 18:05.283
Bible photographer.

18:05.285 --> 18:07.018
Okay, we're smiling,

18:07.020 --> 18:09.287
we're happy to
see Jesus.

18:09.289 --> 18:11.355
There we go.

18:11.357 --> 18:12.957
Hey, guys,
watch your step in there.

18:12.959 --> 18:15.927
That floor's gonna be dripping
in virgin olive oil.

18:15.929 --> 18:17.462
That's kinda hot.
Gross.

18:17.464 --> 18:21.099
Hello, we are
the three wise men.

18:21.101 --> 18:23.201
We came here
following a star.

18:23.203 --> 18:25.269
Those two statements
contradict each other.

18:25.271 --> 18:27.071
We also come
bearing gifts.

18:27.073 --> 18:28.439
I brought frankincense.

18:28.441 --> 18:29.540
I brought myrrh.

18:29.542 --> 18:31.309
And I brought you
a breast pump,

18:31.311 --> 18:33.544
which in these times
is just a guy.

18:33.546 --> 18:34.979
When do I start?

18:34.981 --> 18:37.048
Oh he's coming!

18:37.050 --> 18:39.117
Oh, it hurts so bad!

18:39.119 --> 18:40.751
God, I hate working
on Christmas.

18:40.753 --> 18:42.553
Oh, here he comes.

18:45.757 --> 18:48.493
And... BC turns to AD!

18:48.495 --> 18:50.294
How's everybody doing?

18:50.296 --> 18:51.996
Oh, he's a miracle!

18:51.998 --> 18:54.565
Hey, if you're a virgin, how
come I shot out of there

18:54.567 --> 18:56.667
like a greased-up
cannonball?

18:56.669 --> 18:58.736
Greetings!
I have come to see

18:58.738 --> 19:02.573
the newborn king, but sadly,
I bring no gift.

19:02.575 --> 19:04.275
Well, what do you got
in your hand there?

19:04.277 --> 19:05.943
Uh, my drum.

19:05.945 --> 19:07.512
Well, then it looks like
you got him a drum.

19:07.514 --> 19:10.748
Pretty good gift.
But this is all I own.

19:10.750 --> 19:12.950
It's what makes me
the "Little Drummer Boy."

19:12.952 --> 19:15.920
Yeah, the baby
wants the drum.

19:15.922 --> 19:18.189
Yeah! Drum!

19:18.191 --> 19:20.658
Okay, nobody touch my hair.
I'm growing it out.

19:20.660 --> 19:22.493
Also, I'm gonna start dieting
and working out

19:22.495 --> 19:24.028
so I'm like crazy lean

19:24.030 --> 19:25.997
for the, you know, for, for,
for the thing.

19:25.999 --> 19:27.265
(hoofbeats approaching)

19:27.267 --> 19:28.432
What the deuce?

19:30.469 --> 19:33.204
Bring out the Christ Child!
We want him!

19:33.206 --> 19:34.138
Uh-oh.

19:34.140 --> 19:35.840
(whirring)

19:40.946 --> 19:44.849
I may have a virgin mom,
but I am one bad mother.

19:48.220 --> 19:50.254
(horse whinnies)

19:57.829 --> 19:59.797
Ah! Ah! You guys get him!
You guys get him!

19:59.799 --> 20:01.232
I forgot something
at the palace!

20:03.702 --> 20:06.404
Pa-choo! Pa-choo!
(makes explosion sound)

20:06.406 --> 20:08.739
And that is the
story of Jesus.

20:08.741 --> 20:10.508
That was awesome, Dad!

20:10.510 --> 20:11.876
Oh, my God! I
just realized

20:11.878 --> 20:14.345
that's the same Jesus as
the Jesus from church!

20:14.347 --> 20:16.047
That's a beautiful story,
Peter,

20:16.049 --> 20:17.548
about people coming together

20:17.550 --> 20:19.717
to form something
greater than themselves.

20:19.719 --> 20:21.252
(knocking on door)

20:22.221 --> 20:23.154
Yes, can I help you?

20:23.156 --> 20:24.522
Hi. We're from out of town

20:24.524 --> 20:26.090
and our car
just broke down!

20:26.092 --> 20:28.025
My wife's in labor.
Can we use your phone?

20:28.027 --> 20:29.060
What?! No!

20:29.062 --> 20:32.196
Couple of freaking scumbags
working some scam,

20:32.198 --> 20:34.031
saying how they want
to use our phone.

20:34.033 --> 20:36.701
What?! Do they want all the
presents under the tree, too?!

20:36.703 --> 20:37.835
Get rid of 'em!

20:37.837 --> 20:39.937
They're not gonna
do that, are they?

20:39.939 --> 20:41.672
Dad, shut the door,
it's freezing!

20:41.674 --> 20:43.040
Please, you've
gotta help us!

20:43.042 --> 20:44.275
You're lucky
it's Christmas

20:44.277 --> 20:46.110
or I'd call the cops on
you dirty grifters!

20:46.112 --> 20:49.213
Now you and your whore
wife get out of here!

20:49.215 --> 20:53.184
Peter, you handled
that perfectly.

20:53.186 --> 20:54.919
Merry Christmas,
Lois.

20:54.921 --> 20:57.255
MAN:
Please!
We're begging you!

20:57.257 --> 20:58.823
I'm getting
the baseball bat.
